sentences: Grażyna Brodzińska née Wayda (b. May 5, 1951 in Cracow) is a Polish soprano, opera and operetta singer, and musical actress, nicknamed The First Lady of Polish Operetta.
Brodzińska was born on May 5, 1951, in Cracow, the daughter of director Edmund Wayda and opera singer Irena Brodzińska.
Grażyna Brodzińska performed at Musical Theatre in Gdynia (1969–1976) and later at Musical Theatre in Szczecin, Warsaw Operetta and Roma Theatre in Warsaw.
Since 2002 Brodzińska is an actress of Silesian Operetta in Gliwice.
In 1960s she graduated from Danuta Baduszkowa's Actors Studio in Gdynia.
